t species** found on every continent except Australia and Antarctica."},"groundingChunkIndices": [4]},{"segment": {"startIndex": 231,"endIndex": 254,"text": "### Key Characteristics"},"groundingChunkIndices": [5,6,7,3,8,9,4,10,11,12,1,0]},{"segment": {"startIndex": 255,"endIndex": 354,"text": "*   **Physical Traits:** They have long, slim bodies, webbed feet for swimming, and powerful tails."},"groundingChunkIndices": [0,4,7]},{"segment": {"startIndex": 355,"endIndex": 459,"text": "Their fur is the densest in the animal kingdom, providing insulation since they lack a layer of blubber."},"groundingChunkIndices": [3,12]},{"segment": {"startIndex": 460,"endIndex": 600,"text": "*   **Diet:** They are active hunters that primarily eat fish, but also consume crustaceans, frogs, and occasionally small birds or mammals."},"groundingChunkIndices": [0,1,9,2,7]},{"segment": {"startIndex": 601,"endIndex": 735,"text": "*   **Behavior:** Known for being highly intelligent and playful, they often engage in activities like sliding down mud or snow banks."},"groundingChunkIndices": [9]},{"segment": {"startIndex": 736,"endIndex": 828,"text": "Some species, like sea otters, are famous for using stones as tools to crack open shellfish."},"groundingChunkIndices": [0,10]},{"segment": {"startIndex": 829,"endIndex": 917,"text": "*   **Social Life:** While many river otters are solitary, others live in family groups."},"groundingChunkIndices": [0,4,12,9]},{"segment": {"startIndex": 1047,"endIndex": 1062,"text": "### Major Types"},"groundingChunkIndices": [5,6,8,1]},{"segment": {"startIndex": 1063,"endIndex": 1147,"text": "*   **River Otters:** Found in freshwater habitats like rivers, lakes, and wetlands."},"groundingChunkIndices": [4,2,11,6]},{"segment": {"startIndex": 1148,"endIndex": 1184,"text": "They spend significant time on land."},"groundingChunkIndices": [8,0,4]},{"segment": {"startIndex": 1185,"endIndex": 1280,"text": "*   **Sea Otters:** Almost entirely aquatic, living in the coastal waters of the North Pacific."},"groundingChunkIndices": [8]},{"segment": {"startIndex": 1281,"endIndex": 1371,"text": "They are a "keystone species," vital for maintaining the health of kelp forest ecosystems."},"groundingChunkIndices": [10]}],"webSearchQueries": ["what do otters eat and their behavior","brief facts about otters","types of otters and their habitats"]}}],"usageMetadata": {"promptTokenCount": 12,"candidatesTokenCount": 329,"totalTokenCount": 341,"promptTokensDetails": [{"modality": "TEXT","tokenCount": 12}]},"modelVersion": "gemini-3-flash-preview","responseId": "MaKsafafNInXjuMPg43i0Qg"}

